Set up binary distribution for macOS and Linux.

Targets:
- macOS arm64 (Apple Silicon)
- macOS amd64 (Intel)
- Linux arm64
- Linux amd64

Tasks:
- GitHub Actions workflow triggered on version tags (e.g. v0.1.0)
- Use goreleaser or raw go build cross-compilation to produce binaries for all four targets
- Attach binaries to GitHub Release
- Homebrew tap formula that points at the GitHub Release artifacts
  so macOS users can install with: brew install <tap>/chipper

This ticket is not blocking any other work — build and install locally
via `go install` until this is in place.

